Kaveel Singh, News24One person was killed after a Mercedes Benz and Audi TT collided on the M4 in Durban. (Supplied, Marshall Security) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; One person was killed after a Mercedes Benz and an Audi TT collided at high speed on the M4 between La Lucia and Umhlanga on Sunday, a security company said.Marshall Security spokesperson Kyle Van Reenen said the 30-year-old driver of the Audi died on impact.Van Reenen said the driver of the Mercedes was stabilised by Netcare 911 paramedics before being freed from his vehicle with the Jaws of Life.&ldquo;Once extricated, the man was taken to a nearby hospital under constant care of an advanced life support paramedic.&rdquo;Van Reenen said the road was closed for over two hours to allow for emergency services to work. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.